 and can thus help to ease the painstaking work of language comparison. Dissertations in Language and Cognition This series explores issues of mental representation, lingustic structure and representation, and their interplay. The research presented in this series is grounded in the idea explored in the Collaborative Research Center 'The structure of representations in language, cognition and science' (SFB 991) that there is a universal format for the representation of linguistic and cognitive concepts.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 25. Feb 2021) 4aDefinition of Sequences. 4aSequence Comparison. 4aSequence Differences. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / General.2bisacsh  aAlignment Analyses.  aAutomatic Cognate Detection.  aAutomatic Cognates Detection.  aBasic Algorithm.  aCollaborative Research Center.  aContinuous Entities.  aDefinition of Sequences.  aDifferences between Sequences.  aDiscrete Entities.  aGerhard Schurz.  aHana Filip.  aHeinrich-Heine-Universität.  aHistorical Linguistics.  aLaura Kallmeyer.  aLexStat.  aLexical Change.  aModelling Sequence Differences.  aMultilingual Cognate Detection.  aMultiple Alignment Analyses.  aPairwise Alignment Analyses.  aPeter Indefrey.  aPhonetic Alignment.  aProgressive Alignment.  aRelations between Languages.  aRelations between Words.  aResemblances in Form.  aResemblances in Meaning.  aRobert D. Van Valin.  aSCA.  aSFB 991.  aSebastian Löbner.  aSemantic Change.  aSequence Comparison.  aSequence Modelling.  aSound Change.  aSound-Class Based Phonetic Alignment.  aStructural Extensions.  aSubstantial Extensions.  aThe 